This paper is primarily focused on the intersection of natural language processing and computer vision, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning algorithms to train agents to navigate through environments, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the creation of a new dataset for evaluating instruction following in navigation tasks, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of robotics in navigation tasks, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics).
